{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-27T19:44:23.364Z","evidence":{"commit":"ff57022e871290593acc75f8cd864ba4de113b64"},"relates_to":["mx-3df5c5"],"content":"Handlers monolith split phase 2 (warren-a2b4 / pl-9088 step 2): src/server/handlers/index.ts вҶ’ runs.ts (789 lines) + plan-runs.ts (484 lines). Pattern matches phase 1 (mx-3df5c5): ROUTE_TABLE stays in handlers/index.ts as the canonical wire surface for gen:docs / gen:openapi; shared helpers (readJsonBody[OrEmpty], requireString, optionalString, requireParam, parseBoolean, parseNonNegativeInt, assertPlotIdDispatchable, defaultSpawn) are exported from index.ts and cross-imported. Streaming plumbing (bridgeAbort/asNdjsonStream/eventToNdjson) lives in runs.ts and is re-exported for plan-runs.ts since both NDJSON tails share it вҖ” keeping it adjacent to streamRunEventsHandler (the larger consumer) rather than hoisting to index.ts. Tests: relocated handlers.plan-runs.test.ts вҶ’ handlers/plan-runs.test.ts and removed its biome noExcessiveLinesPerFunction override by splitting the monolithic POST /plan-runs describe into three siblings (core + Plot integration (warren-b89f) + plot_id validation (warren-bae5)) sharing a setupPlanRunFixture() factory. Helpers (poolFor, depsFor, makeBurrowClient) are duplicated between runs.test.ts and the residual handlers.test.ts because both files retain describes that use them вҖ” splitting helpers into a shared module would have leaked test-only plumbing across multiple files.","id":"mx-99ad0d"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-27T20:25:54.740Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-ea0c","commit":"ed47012f666066f4b3c04ddcac74b9054a6fbfd0"},"content":"reap.ts monolith split (warren-ea0c / pl-9088 step 4): src/runs/reap.ts (2114 lines) + reap.test.ts (2792 lines) вҶ’ src/runs/reap/ subdirectory with per-sub-step modules. Pattern mirrors handlers split (mx-3df5c5/mx-99ad0d/mx-929bbc): index.ts is the re-export shim + module-level doc-comment; types.ts pulls the public interfaces into their own file so they can be imported without dragging the orchestrator's transitive imports; run.ts holds the reapRun orchestrator after extracting three helpers (runPreviewLaunch + runPreviewAnnotate in preview.ts, runPrOpen in pr-open.ts, dispatchAutoPlanRuns in auto-plan-run.ts) to fit under the 500-line threshold; pure helpers (mergeMulchFile, mergePlotEventsFile, mergePlotJsonFile) re-export through index.ts so external consumers (src/runs/index.ts) only change the import path suffix. Tests split alongside: each .test.ts sits next to its module and references shared fixtures via reap/test-helpers.ts (fakeFs, fakeExec, fakeBurrowClient, fakeOpenPr, setup, makePool, makeBurrow, Ctx + re-exported bun-side types). The four complex functions still over Biome's noExcessiveCognitiveComplexity ceiling (mergeMulch, mergePlot, mirrorSeeds, mirrorPlans, reapRun) carry over to the override block under their new module paths вҖ” refactoring those algorithms was explicitly out of scope for the mechanical split.","id":"mx-cdd0ca"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-28T04:05:22.896Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-6bf6","commit":"56a30a2ba61ed1f0f090eb03b9576e3384402b50"},"content":"Split src/plan-runs/coordinator.test.ts (804 lines) into coordinator.test-helpers.ts and four focused per-phase test files (coordinator.dispatch.test.ts, coordinator.gating.test.ts, coordinator.resume.test.ts, coordinator.completion.test.ts) under 500 lines to remove its file-size budget","id":"mx-bfddb2"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-29T01:08:55.801Z","evidence":{"commit":"edf067c56175c450f6213b95f5db526326a8a5a7"},"dir_anchors":["src/runs/reap"],"content":"runWorkspaceDestroy (src/runs/reap/destroy.ts, warren-0d89) is reap's final sub-step: after the terminal-state transition + reap.completed emit, it calls client.http.burrows.destroy(burrowId,{archive:true}) via withTransportMapping, deletes the warren burrows row (repos.burrows.delete), and emits reap.workspace_destroyed {burrowId,archived,deletedEvents,deletedMessages,deletedRuns}. Best-effort like the other sub-steps (fail()->reap_failed step=workspace_destroy, never blocks the run). Skips (emits reap.workspace_destroy_skipped) for interactive runs and live/starting previews (previewLaunchState==='live' or run.previewState in starting/live); skips silently when burrowId or workerClient is null. Surfaces workspaceDestroyed:boolean on ReapRunResult. Fixes the 2026-05-27 disk-full incident where 122 stale burrow workspaces filled the Fly volume. The DELETE /burrows/:id wire response is DestroyBurrowResult (no workspaceRemoved field вҖ” that lives only on burrow's in-process destroyBurrowFully), so the event reports archived as a boolean + deleted counts.","id":"mx-2598a1"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-29T04:06:40.539Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-27d3","commit":"c3bcb3a8172451a7deb5d96e8483e5ccab083b77"},"content":"All warren-authored reap-time bookkeeping commits now pass --no-verify so project git hooks (e.g. a pre-commit running the full check:all gauntlet) never block them. Covered: src/runs/reap/stage.ts (chore(warren): plot state, chore(warren): seeds state) and src/plots/sync.ts (plot sync: update plot metadata). --no-verify sits immediately after the 'commit' subcommand arg. Agent-authored commits inside the sandbox are deliberately NOT bypassed (warren-27d3).","id":"mx-93385f"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-29T04:14:53.768Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-88da","commit":"db1893a52a3c6e02da0964a13603b51c1aa19c82"},"content":"warren-88da / pl-369d: the 'functions coverage drop below 85%' bug no longer reproduces вҖ” sibling step warren-f65e already ratcheted floors up to functions 87.09 / lines 90.32 after coverage was restored by the handlers/stream/preview splits. Current coverage is functions 87.62 / lines 90.83 (both green). Hardened the resolution by covering both exported functions in src/runs/stream/terminal-detect.ts (was 50% func / 63% lines): added isPiAgentEnd tests plus the claude-code result branch and null/non-object payload guards, lifting that module to 100/100.","id":"mx-2107b5"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-29T05:18:19.738Z","evidence":{"commit":"ee30e45dbe78d42e1ca9b6a9cd940db5ab0b9518"},"content":"buildRunMetrics (src/runs/analytics/run-metrics.ts, warren-368e / pl-ad0f step 1) is the pure run-level analytics aggregator mirroring cost-analytics.ts: takes RunMetricsRow[] (one per runs row, w/ provider/model pre-extracted from frontmatter + seedId) and emits totals (run/state counts, successRate over terminal runs only, avg/median/p95 durationMs via nearest-rank percentile, contextTokens + cost StatSummaries), timeSeries (per-day buckets w/ per-state counts, NONE_KEY for null startedAt sorted last), byAgent/byModel/byProvider RunGroupBuckets ranked by total context desc, byFailureReason (failed runs only), topSeedsByContext (excludes null seedId per risk #4). Conventions: contextTokens = tokensInput + tokensCacheRead (null only when BOTH null, excluded from averages not counted as 0 per risk #3); durationMsOf returns null unless both timestamps valid + non-negative; NONE_KEY='__none__' folds null group keys. Step 2 (warren-0692) wires the GET /analytics/runs handler.","id":"mx-c29736"}
{"type":"pattern","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-29T18:06:35.478Z","evidence":{"commit":"457d0b15059955b4df95c304377f6ae29e40a013"},"dir_anchors":["src/server/main"],"name":"fallback-workspace-gc","description":"Fallback workspace GC (warren-0a9a): src/runs/reap/gc.ts sweeps the burrows placement table for rows whose runs are ALL terminal and whose newest activity (latest terminal endedAt, else burrows.added_at) is older than WARREN_WORKSPACE_GC_TTL (default 1h), then calls client.http.burrows.destroy(archive:true) + repos.burrows.delete per row. Complements per-reap workspace_destroy (warren-0d89) for crash-mid-reap / force-killed cases. Pure predicate findStrandedBurrows + buildBurrowActivity(activeRuns,terminalRuns) reduce listByState(queued/running/paused) and listByState(succeeded/failed/cancelled) rows вҖ” NO new RunsRepo aggregate methods (avoids growing runs.ts past its frozen 610-line file-size budget; first attempt added activeBurrowIds()/latestEndedAtByBurrow() and blew the ratchet). Worker startWorkspaceGcWorker mirrors startPreviewEvictionWorker: single-flight, NOOP_HANDLE when disabled, stop() drains in-flight. Wired in src/server/main/index.ts (config + worker + teardown); config threaded as ServerDeps.workspaceGcTtlMs. Shared findStrandedBurrows backs the stale_burrow_workspaces diagnostic in src/diagnostics/stale-workspaces.ts (separate file, NOT checks.ts which is at its 616-line frozen budget) surfaced via warren doctor + GET /readyz.","files":[".env.example","CHANGELOG.md","src/cli/commands/doctor.test.ts","src/cli/commands/doctor.ts","src/diagnostics/stale-workspaces.test.ts","src/diagnostics/stale-workspaces.ts","src/runs/reap/gc.test.ts","src/runs/reap/gc.ts","src/server/handlers/diagnostics.ts","src/server/main/deps.ts","src/server/main/index.ts","src/server/main/logging.ts","src/server/types.ts"],"id":"mx-4b8aac"}
{"type":"pattern","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-29T19:04:37.393Z","evidence":{"commit":"03499f0ad1ae8709321fa8452c9ce43bf4732b80"},"dir_anchors":["src/db/schema"],"name":"run-replicate-clone-from","description":"Re-run/clone (warren-e96f): POST /runs accepts cloneFromRunId to replicate a prior run's agent/model/project/prompt against the project default base. Shares runs.parent_run_id with continuation (warren-4b11) but discriminates via the new runs.clone_kind enum ('replicate' vs 'continue'). spawnRun's resolveContinuationRef branches on input.cloneKind: 'replicate' returns the explicit ref (not the parent's pushed branch); default/'continue' recomposes burrow/<parentId>. Handler derives effective provider/model via readProviderFrontmatter off the parent's frozen rendered_agent_json so the replica fires onto the exact same model.","files":[".canopy/agent.json","src/client/client.ts","src/client/types.ts","src/db/migrations/meta/_journal.json","src/db/migrations/postgres/meta/_journal.json","src/db/repos/runs.ts","src/db/schema/columns.ts","src/db/schema/postgres.ts","src/db/schema/sqlite.ts","src/runs/spawn/dispatch.ts","src/runs/spawn/types.ts","src/server/handlers/runs.dispatch.test.ts","src/server/handlers/runs/dispatch.ts","src/ui/src/api/types.ts","src/ui/src/pages/NewRun.tsx","src/ui/src/pages/RunDetail.tsx"],"id":"mx-3abba0"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-29T19:16:50.024Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-05ea","commit":"7f60a01699ee722dc9140da40c6b85c14872798d"},"content":"composeRunBranch (src/runs/branch.ts) takes an optional 3rd arg targetBranch (warren-05ea): a non-empty/non-whitespace value short-circuits the ${prefix}/${runId} composition so a CI-fixer run pushes to the existing PR branch; empty/whitespace falls back to the composed branch so a stray config never strands a spawn on a blank ref.","id":"mx-51eddb"}
{"type":"decision","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-30T05:57:09.503Z","evidence":{"commit":"761f00024363b5988dee2df83d0bb61f3ba6dca2"},"dir_anchors":["src/runs/reap","src/seeds-cli"],"title":"Plan-run coordinator fails terminally on a definitive missing-seed (warren-0fed)","rationale":"An infinite retryable noop on a not-found child seed spammed plan_run.noop and wedged plan-runs in 'running' forever; a definitive not-found is unrecoverable so it must be terminal, but transient sd failures (timeout/lock) must stay retryable so a hung seed store doesn't kill healthy plan-runs.","id":"mx-d95b87"}
{"type":"pattern","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-30T06:02:49.021Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-41d5","commit":"b6faa36d646f4489c4af87849a574e6035a34d81"},"dir_anchors":["src/runs/reap"],"name":"auto_plan_run child-seed validation","description":"auto_plan_run reap path (src/runs/reap/auto-plan-run.ts dispatchAutoPlanRuns, warren-41d5) now validates each new plan's child seeds via showSeed before creating a plan-run, mirroring the manual POST /plan-runs handler: SeedNotFoundError on any child -> skip the plan + emit auto_plan_run_skipped {planId, reason:'missing_child_seeds', missing}; all-children-closed -> skip with reason 'all_children_closed'; transient sd errors propagate to fail('auto_plan_run'). Gated on an optional seedsCli?: SeedsCliDeps seam threaded ReapRunInput -> run.ts -> CreateBridgeRegistryInput (bridges.ts) -> RunWithReconnectInput (bridge-reconnect.ts), wired in main/index.ts bootBridges (reusing the coordinator's {sdBinary: schedulerConfig.sdBinary, spawn: defaultSpawn}) + cli/commands/run.ts. Absent seedsCli = no validation (legacy unit tests unchanged). Depends on warren-0fed's SeedNotFoundError discriminator.","files":[".gitignore","src/cli/commands/run.ts","src/runs/reap/auto-plan-run.test.ts","src/runs/reap/auto-plan-run.ts","src/runs/reap/run.ts","src/runs/reap/types.ts","src/server/bridge-reconnect.ts","src/server/bridges.ts","src/server/main/index.ts"],"id":"mx-d11503"}
{"type":"pattern","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-06-05T22:21:03.343Z","evidence":{"commit":"58a1deef32ecae25c0d24b07ae00135eb4ab2d20"},"name":"run-heartbeat-watchdog","description":"Run heartbeat watchdog (warren-285d): src/runs/watchdog.ts force-fails 'running' runs that go silent-but-busy (e.g. a runaway quality-gate command behind a stuck bash tool вҖ” biome pinning cores, exitCode null, no new events). tickWatchdog scans repos.runs.listByState('running'), computes idleMs = now - newest-event-ts (computeIdleMs falls back to startedAt; null when no parseable anchor), and when idleMs >= heartbeatTimeoutMs runs forceFail: emit watchdog.timed_out system event (WATCHDOG_TIMED_OUT_KIND), best-effort POST /runs/:burrow_run_id/cancel (swallows BurrowNotFoundError + transport errors), then reapRun({outcome:'failed', failureReason:'timed_out'}). Routing through reap (not bare finalize) is deliberate: reap's workspace_destroy sub-step destroys the burrow workspace which tears down the bwrap process tree (the cancel-doesn't-reap-tree gap), and reap still pushes partial work вҖ” same philosophy as cancelRun (warren-a69a). Opt-in via WARREN_RUN_HEARTBEAT_TIMEOUT_MS>0 (loadWatchdogConfigFromEnv; tick WARREN_WATCHDOG_TICK_MS default 30000). bootWatchdog mirrors bootPauseDetector single-flight wrapper. Wired in src/server/main/detector-wiring.ts (bootWatchdogFromEnv + bootPauseDetectorFromEnv extracted from index.ts to stay under the 500-line file-size budget); teardown order planRunCoordinator -> pauseDetector -> watchdog -> scheduler. 'timed_out' was already a reserved RUN_FAILURE_REASONS value (src/db/schema/columns.ts) awaiting this deadline-based reaper.","files":[".canopy/agent.json",".env.example","src/db/schema/columns.ts","src/runs/index.ts","src/server/main/index.ts"],"id":"mx-e928fb"}
{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-06-06T09:22:23.214Z","evidence":{"commit":"476a504a263c4109be0710efc910142f8c8bbba2"},"content":"warren-c770 / LEVERET.md В§0.4: the pi-chat runtime suppresses the per-turn agent_end terminal envelope, so a conversation run stays non-terminal across turns. Three warren-side lifetime guards gained an explicit conversation skip: (1) heartbeat watchdog (src/runs/watchdog.ts) вҖ” 'if (run.mode===\"conversation\") continue' before computeIdleMs so an armed WARREN_RUN_HEARTBEAT_TIMEOUT_MS can't force-fail idle conversations; (2) reap workspace-destroy (src/runs/reap/destroy.ts) вҖ” extends the interactive exemption to conversation, emitting reap.workspace_destroy_skipped reason 'conversation_run'; (3) bootBridges crash-recovery (src/server/bridges.ts) вҖ” on a pre-probe 404 for a conversation run, skip the bridge with reason 'conversation_burrow_lost' WITHOUT calling reconcileLostBurrowRun, leaving the row non-terminal so re-wake (warren-6ccf) replays the transcript. Pause detector (pause.ts guards mode!=='batch') and workspace GC (state-keyed) already exempt conversation for free. Also added 'conversation' to RUN_MODES in src/db/schema/columns.ts.","id":"mx-b41dbd"}
{"type":"pattern","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-06-06T09:51:42.528Z","evidence":{"commit":"9340f0cdd830bf670279c1689951e071a2c0d50f"},"name":"conversation-rewake-seam-primitive","description":"Leveret build-phase-2 lifetime/re-wake primitives (conversation-idle.ts, conversation-rewake.ts) are landed as pure orchestration + seam interfaces (reader/rotator/spawner) BEFORE the warren-0b91 conversations/messages tables exist. rewakeConversation() takes a ConversationRewakeReader + ConversationAnchorRotator seam and an injectable RewakeSpawner (defaults to spawnRun), so unit tests stay disk/table-free; production repo-backed impls slot in at the HTTP boundary (warren-af15). Re-wake refuses non-active conversations and non-terminal anchoring runs, replays the full DB transcript verbatim via buildRewakePrompt into a fresh mode:'conversation' spawnRun, rotates anchoring_run_id, then emits conversation.rewake_replayed. No pi --session resume / old burrow dependency.","id":"mx-ab5467"}
{"type":"failure","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-06-06T10:12:10.161Z","evidence":{"commit":"15a0252051e2e27c516546389bf3d7ad2d1ed1c5"},"description":"warren-ce65 (conversation stream-bridge: persist turns to messages + parse propose_intent from tool_execution_end + write intent_edited(actor=agent:leveret) host-side) is hard-blocked by two unmet dependencies as of 2026-06-06. (1) warren-0b91 NOT implemented: no conversations/messages tables in src/db/schema/sqlite.ts and no MessagesRepo/ConversationsRepo in src/db/repos/, so message-turn persistence is impossible. (2) The ../plot ACL widening (EVENT_ACL.intent_edited -> ['user','agent']) NOT shipped: published @os-eco/plot-cli@0.4.0 still pins intent_edited:['user'] (asserted in its own acl.test.ts) and assertCanEmit rejects agents ('agents must surface a question_posed event instead of mutating intent'). warren's facade also still lists intent_edited in HUMANS_ONLY_EVENT_TYPES (src/plot-client/types.ts). An agent:leveret intent_edited write throws at both facade and lib runtime. The plot repo is not co-mounted (no ../plot; origin is warren only) so the ACL cannot be widened from this run.","resolution":"Leave ce65 open. Sequence: (a) land warren-0b91 first (tables+repos), (b) ship the ACL widening in ../plot and publish a plot-cli bump, (c) pin the bump in package.json + remove intent_edited from HUMANS_ONLY_EVENT_TYPES in src/plot-client/types.ts and add editIntent/agent-intent surface to AgentPlotHandle, (d) then build the conversation bridge variant. No fabricated partial committed because any wired slice would either fail check:deps (unused export) or throw at the ACL boundary.","id":"mx-e79c70"}
{"type":"pattern","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-06-06T11:39:05.020Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-b872","commit":"2bdc517c021809a37549ebfb8d26c6da4cdfe918"},"name":"Send-off merge poller (warren-b872)","description":"src/runs/conversation-merge-poller.ts polls closed conversations carrying a submitted_pr_url whose planner_run_id is still null (ConversationsRepo.listAwaitingPlannerDispatch), reuses src/plan-runs/pr-merge.ts createPrMergeChecker for retry-aware merge probes, and on merge auto-dispatches the planner keyed on plot_id via the PlannerDispatchFn seam. recordPlannerDispatch is a single-shot guard (writes only when planner_run_id IS NULL, returns null on a second call) so a re-detect never double-dispatches. Boot wrapper bootConversationMergePoller mirrors bootPauseDetector single-flight; createMergePollerDispatch (conversation-merge-dispatch.ts) wraps spawnRun+bridges.start like createPlanRunSpawn. Opt-in via WARREN_MERGE_POLLER_ENABLED=1, tick WARREN_MERGE_POLLER_TICK_MS (default 30s).","files":["src/db/migrations/meta/_journal.json","src/db/migrations/postgres/meta/_journal.json","src/db/repos/conversations.test.ts","src/db/repos/conversations.ts","src/db/schema/postgres.ts","src/db/schema/sqlite.ts","src/runs/index.ts","src/server/main/detector-wiring.ts","src/server/main/index.ts"],"id":"mx-a3cec3"}
{"type":"decision","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-06-06T12:07:15.761Z","evidence":{"commit":"8c36fe13d637031c40e2f10e6a10172571806620"},"dir_anchors":["src/registry/builtins","src/runs","src/runs/reap","src/server/handlers"],"title":"Retired mode=interactive / brainstorm path (warren-d622)","rationale":"LEVERET.md В§0.8 last-phase cleanup: intent shaping migrated to conversations (steerRun channel); keeping the dead respawn-per-turn primitive was pure liability once conversation parity landed.","id":"mx-967abe"}
{"type":"failure","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-06-06T21:10:17.582Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-005d","commit":"9c717e85e74fdc37c1c045903a7d83236d05e954"},"dir_anchors":["src/runs"],"description":"warren-005d's coordinator (PR #266) landed src/runs/conversation-idle.ts + the conversation.idleTimeoutMs knob fully tested but NEVER BOOTED вҖ” bootConversationIdleDetector had no production caller, so idle conversation runs would run forever. When a seed ships a 'boot-worker', verify the wiring in src/server/main/detector-wiring.ts + bootServer stop chain, not just the module.","resolution":"Added createRepoIdleConversationReader (repo-backed reader: active conversations joined against a running anchoring run) co-located in conversation-idle.ts mirroring defaultPlotEventReader, plus bootConversationIdleDetectorFromEnv in detector-wiring.ts вҖ” ON by default (lifecycle reclaim like preview eviction / workspace GC, NOT opt-in like pause/watchdog/merge-poller), opt-out WARREN_CONVERSATION_IDLE_DISABLED=1, tick WARREN_CONVERSATION_IDLE_TICK_MS default 60s; handle stopped in bootServer teardown.","id":"mx-384f2d"}
{"type":"pattern","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-06-06T22:49:27.798Z","evidence":{"issue":"warren-70c6","commit":"a89346e80aa46cbcee16acb2e79944da91dbe8c6"},"name":"PR-open retry with injectable sleep seam","description":"warren-70c6: openPullRequest (src/runs/pr.ts) embeds errors[] JSON in the message for non-already-exists 422 failures so operators can diagnose transient vs permanent errors. runPrOpen (src/runs/reap/pr-open.ts) wraps tryOpenPr in a bounded retry loop (3 retries, delays 1s/2s/4s) for http_error results that are not the permanent 'no commits between' 422 shape. A sleep seam (RunPrOpenInput.sleep) is threaded from ReapRunInput through run.ts so tests inject a no-op and avoid real delays. isRetryablePrResult returns false for missing_token and network errors (surface immediately) and for permanent 422s.","files":["src/runs/reap/pr-open.ts","src/runs/reap/types.ts","src/runs/reap/run.ts","src/runs/pr.ts"],"id":"mx-756a36"}

{"type":"convention","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-15T17:16:57.743Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-b3d8","commit":"dfe272e7145768d31aa61178e6e434ca262893bb"},"content":"When a ROADMAP R-XX ships, update its status line in-place with 'Status: [shipped] вҖ” landed via plan pl-XXXX (parent seed warren-XXXX), YYYY-MM-DD.' then a concrete summary of what shipped (migration filenames, new routes, schema PK changes, frontmatter labels, UI surfaces, acceptance scenario number). Convert the 'Open questions.' subsection to 'Follow-ups (filed as seeds; not in V1).' once those questions are filed as seeds in the plan's docs step. Examples: R-02 (pl-5d74), R-06 (pl-2f15), R-03 (pl-fef5).","id":"mx-5ac8fb"}
{"type":"reference","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-15T17:18:43.536Z","evidence":{"seeds":"warren-2842","commit":"ea9a6820322d2b6e0628a3d7855808ef671f989f"},"relates_to":["mx-dd2b4e"],"name":"pl-fef5 R-03 per-project canopy tier shipped clean","description":"R-03 (warren-2842) shipped via 11-step plan pl-fef5 over 2026-05-15 with bun test (1361 pass / 15 skip / 0 fail), biome check --error-on-warnings, and tsc --noEmit all green on the final wrap-up step (warren-b21a) with no follow-up fixes. Schema migration (step 1, warren-094a) dropped agents.name PK + runs.agent_name FK for composite identity (project_id, name) plus partial unique on (name) WHERE project_id IS NULL, applied cleanly on both sqlite and postgres. Two follow-up seeds filed in step 10 (warren-b3d8): cross-tier inheritance (project extends library/builtin) and on-disk rendered cache under <projectPath>/.canopy/.rendered/, both intentionally deferred from V2 scope. Reference point for future schema-touching plans: step-by-step decomposition with green gates per merge avoided integration debt.","files":[".seeds/issues.jsonl"],"id":"mx-020240"}
{"type":"decision","classification":"tactical","recorded_at":"2026-05-17T19:49:11.181Z","evidence":{"commit":"d734c5853c26c9829def22de34ba61963df1c611"},"tags":["plot","network-topology","post-v1"],"title":"Adopt Plot as warren's coordination primitive","rationale":"The blog post 'Agentic Networks' (jayminwest.com/blog/12-agentic-networks) argues for a network topology with humans as peer nodes sharing a substrate, not orchestrators above workers. Plot is that substrate. Warren's current run-centric model reifies the hierarchical pattern; shifting to Plot-centric makes the network topology buildable. Plot ships as a standalone os-eco repo (not incubated inside warren) to avoid extraction switching costs (mulch re-domaining, comment rewrites, API reshaping) and to enable agent-side CLI use directly from sandboxes.","id":"mx-39fd5c"}
